Sending e-mail from Python script
(1)	Create g-mail account
(2)	Install google client libraries into python, https://developers.google.com/gmail/api/quickstart/python
(3)	Massage google account to give access to your script:
You need to create a project https://developers.google.com/workspace/guides/create-project 
You need to create credentials: https://www.thepythoncode.com/article/use-gmail-api-in-python user your own e-mail address
Enable the API: https://developers.google.com/workspace/guides/enable-apis 
(you want gmail api)
Authorization for the API: https://developers.google.com/workspace/guides/auth-overview 
Chose Scope for the script:  https://developers.google.com/workspace/guides/configure-oauth-consent#choose-scopes 
https://developers.google.com/identity/protocols/oauth2/scopes#gmail 
Suggest to go with: https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.modify
Has to be added under API & Services OAuth consent screen (edit app registration)
Test user:  the e-mail address from before 
(4)	Create testing script:
https://developers.google.com/gmail/api/quickstart/python 
